My feeling is that the right solution to multiple rotation blendings is that we will need to have, per rotation track, something like this:

```C++
enum {
  MAX_BLENDS=8
}
struct RotationBlend {
      Quaternion rotation;
      float contribution;
};
RotationBlend blends[MAX_BLENDS];
uint32_t blend_count;
```

And just add the blends one after another. If more than MAX_BLENDS, then just find the one with the minimum contribution and see if greater and replace it.

Afterwards, normalize the contributions (ensure they add up to one) and do as described [here](https://web.archive.org/web/20200707210941/http://wiki.unity3d.com/index.php/Averaging_Quaternions_and_Vectors).

